        stringBuilder.append("                    \"locale\": \"en-us\",\n");
        stringBuilder.append("                    \"translation\": \"<p>If you&#39;re a support manager or other power user, you&#39;ll need\\n  to get to know the admin area of Kayako. The admin area is home\\n  to a lot of workhorse Kayako features, including the automation\\n  engine, branding, and localization tools, and configuration\\n  options for views, fields, and forms.</p>\\n  <p>In this article, we&#39;ll give you a high-level introduction to\\n  the admin area of Kayako. We&#39;ll also highlight some of the\\n  features you may want to try out next, with links off to other\\n  areas of the user guide.</p>\\n  <h2>Exploring Kayako&#39;s admin features</h2>\\n  <p>When you sign in to Kayako with an administrator account,\\n  you&#39;ll see a gear icon on the top toolbar throughout the agent\\n  area.</p>\\n  <p><img class=\\\"fr-dib fr-draggable\\\" src=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/base/media/url/7dV9RRbBDOskeHntpFV9ANAE7UQCabhQ\\\" alt=\\\"admin area link in agent area\\\"></p>\\n  <p>Clicking on the gear icon will take you into the admin area.\\n  You can also log directly into the admin area by adding &#39;/admin&#39;\\n  to the end of your Help Center URL.</p>\\n  <p>What you see in the admin area will depend on what permissions\\n  your administrator account has. In this article, we&#39;ll cover all\\n  the possible configuration options you&#39;d see if you have full\\n  administrative access.</p>\\n  <p><em>NOTE: To learn more, check our <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1183-assigning-user-roles-to-control-access\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">user guide article about user roles and\\n  permissions</a>.</em></p>\\n  <p>No matter where you are in the admin area, you&#39;ll see a\\n  sidebar menu on the left. Let&#39;s take a quick look at each section\\n  of that menu:</p>\\n  <ul>\\n    <li>\\n      <strong>Channels</strong> — Here you&#39;ll be able to add and\\n      edit the channels you use to communicate with your customers.\\n      You can manage your support team&#39;s <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1147-configuring-email-support\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">email addresses</a>, <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1171-enabling-kayako-messenger\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">Messenger instances</a>, <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1148-setting-up-twitter-support\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">Twitter accounts</a>, <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1149-adding-facebook-support\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">Facebook pages</a>, and <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1170-webhooks\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">incoming webhooks</a> from here.\\n    </li>\\n    <li>\\n      <strong>Apps</strong>— In this section, you&#39;ll find settings\\n      for hooking up Kayako integrations, including communicating\\n      with other apps using <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1169-zapier\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">Zapier</a> or manually creating user-defined\\n      <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1146-defining-custom-endpoints\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">endpoints</a> to enable further integrations.\\n    </li>\\n    <li>\\n      <strong>Manage</strong> — You can use the options in this\\n      section to customize how your team breaks down their workload\\n      with <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1150-adding-and-editing-views\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">views</a>, what kind of information you track\\n      with conversation <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1151-adding-custom-fields-for-conversations-users-and-organizations\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">fields</a> and <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1152-building-forms-for-different-conversation-types\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">forms</a>. In addition, you&#39;ll be able to\\n      build up a collection of reusable replies and updates using\\n      <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1153-automating-common-replies-and-updates-using-macros\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">macros</a>. And if you&#39;re providing <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1154-localization\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">multi-lingual</a> or <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1155-brands\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">multi-brand</a> support from your Kayako, you&#39;ll\\n      find settings for those features here.\\n    </li>\\n    <li>\\n      <strong>People</strong> — The options in this section let you\\n      <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1180-creating-user-accounts\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">add and configure user accounts</a> for both\\n      your support team and your customers. You can also configure\\n      user roles and permissions, and group your users into\\n      <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1156-grouping-staff-users-into-teams\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">staff teams</a> or <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1184-managing-customer-organizations\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">customer organizations</a>.\\n    </li>\\n    <li>\\n      <strong>Automation</strong> — Under this heading you&#39;ll find\\n      options for building powerful automations, including <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1158-establishing-slas-and-escalations\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">SLAs</a> <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1159-creating-automations-with-triggers-and-monitors\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">triggers, and monitors</a>. If you haven&#39;t\\n      gotten started with automation yet, we&#39;d recommend you start\\n      with our <a href=\\\"https://support.kayako.com/article/1167-automation-intro\\\" rel=\\\"nofollow\\\">intro to automation article</a>.\\n    </li>\\n    <li><strong>Account Settings</strong> — This section of the\\n    menu is home to all your Kayako account settings. You&#39;ll be\\n    able to view and edit your account details, change your plan,\\n    and edit your security settings.</li>\\n  </ul>\",\n");
